             is the productive frequency of rearrangement i. Values of Simpson clonality range from 0 to 1 and measure how evenly receptor sequences (rearrangements) are distributed among a set of T cells. Clonality values approaching 0 indicate a very even distribution of frequencies, whereas values approaching 1 indicate an increasingly asymmetric distribution in which a few clones are present at high frequencies.
